<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_764606"><span style="font-size: 24pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>第五步</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 18pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>购买技能</strong></span><br>　　你的人物现在已经有了基本属性，下一步就选好你的技能，它们体现了你的特殊能力和天赋。这部分内容由优先级表的第四竖列囊括。记住在这点上，玩家只剩下两个优先级还未分配，所以他们应该从中为这个竖列选择一个。<br>　　技能被分解为三种类型：行动、知识和语言技能。行动技能是人物可以通过他们的身体做到的事情：使用枪械、驾驶车辆、撒下令人信服的谎言、施放法术、注册幽魂等等。知识技能是人物知道的事情：如何发现狂奔者的藏身处、城市的布局、捷径、街头诊所的位置、如何辨别街头帮派等等。语言技能是人物可以说、写并能理解的语言。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Step Five:<br>Purchase Skills<br>You now have the basic attributes of your character; the next step is to figure out your skills, the areas where you have particular abilities and gifts. This is covered in the fourth column of the Priority Table. Remember that at this point, players should have only two Priority Levels left that have yet to be assigned, so they should choose one of them for this column.<br>&nbsp; Skills are broken down into three types: Active, Knowledge, and Language skills. Active skills are what the character can do physically: use firearms, drive a car, tell convincing lies, cast spells, register sprites, etc. Knowledge skills are what the character knows: how to find runner hangouts, the layout of the city, short cuts, the locations of street clinics, how to identify street gangs, etc. Language skills are the languages the character can speak, write, and comprehend.</div></div></div><br><strong>这些数字意味着什么</strong><br>　　技能竖列的第一个数字是人物用来花费在个别技能上的技能点。这些技能点虽然也可以用于知识和语言技能（见下），但通常用于购买行动技能。如果在这一步中，你没有达到理想的技能等级，那记住在人物创建结束时，技能也可以用业力提升。在这一步中，仅需要一个技能点就能获得一个新的技能或者将一个技能提升一级。<br>　　竖列中的第二个数字显示人物有多少点数能够用在技能组上。技能组把相似或互补的技能打包销售给玩家。当购买技能组时，人物视为在这个技能组中的所有个别技能上都获得这个技能组的等级。在游戏过程中，人物可能希望拆开技能组，只提升其中一个技能，这个随便他，但直到该技能组中的所有技能都再次处于相同的等级之后，他才能够重新以提升技能组的方式提升这些技能。技能组点数不能用于购买个别技能，反之亦然。另外，在这一步中，技能组不能拆解，所以个别技能点不能用于提升已购买的技能组中的技能的等级。（注意技能组可以在“第七步：使用你剩余的业力”中被拆解P.98。）<br>　　在人物创建中，人物最高可以将技能提升至6（如果购买了天资特质就能到7）。在人物完成后，技能最高可以达到12（拥有天资特质则是13）。<br>　　所有技能点数和技能组点数都必须在人物创建中用完。这些点数不能保留到游戏开始之后使用，玩家应确保想要购买的任何个别技能没有在他们已经选取的技能组之中。例如，一位玩家可能想要购买奔跑技能，但如果他已经购买了运动技能组而该组包含了奔跑，那么他就不需要再次购买奔跑技能了。<br>　　除了技能等级，玩家可能还想用他们的点数购买“专精”。专精是技能中人物投入了额外的时间和精力的部分，所以他们应该额外的娴熟于此。例如，如果你拥有利刃技能，你可以专精于斧子或救生刀。专精给予你在专精领域的技能检定中获得+2骰池加值。<br>　　在人物创建时，专精花费1点技能点。每个个别技都不能拥有超过一项以上的专精。当人物提升时，他们可以在额外获得别的领域的专业知识（例如，可以在拥有刀剑专业知识的同时完善斧子的专业知识），然后在同一技能上增加更多的专精。在这一步的购买之后，也可以在人物创建结束时用业力购买专精（见“人物提升”，P.103）。<br>　　技能组不能购买专精。技能组反映了对相似技能的普遍理解而不是如同专精那样特定的专业知识。玩家可以选择为技能组中的个别技能购买专精，但如果他们这样做就会像之前提到的一样拆解掉技能组，意味着这个技能组的所有技能都必须分别提升了。此外，一旦技能组中的一个技能选取了专精，这个技能组就不能够被重建了。在人物创建的第五步不允许如此，你只能在第七步通过购买专精拆解技能组（详见P.98）。<br>　　街头的生存取决于两点（至少）：精通你所擅长的，并且在事情见鬼的时候有后备技能。如果你要成为一个射手，堆高你的枪械技能，但最好再提高一点儿察觉技能，这样你就能看见你的目标，有点儿潜行技能保证他们看不见你，有点儿急救技能以防撞上子弹。如果你是个魔法师，你需要足够高的法术施放技能、法术反制技能可能还有召唤技能，但体操技能可能对于你躲避攻击是个很好的帮助，手上功夫技能在你隐身的时候从守卫身上偷出钥匙卡时会很有用。如果你是个出面人，你需要足够高的社交技能，但如果你不购买一些战斗技能的话，在言辞辜负你的时候，你就会遇上麻烦。无论你是什么人物范型，你都应该从整体上思考你的人物技能，打造一些优秀的技能，同时也保证一个整体的平衡，最大限度的提高你成功的可能。一开始你不会拥有所有的你想要的技能，但那就是你为什么玩这个游戏。当你完成任务赚取更多的业力，你就有机会提升你的技能和属性。<br>　　为便于参考，这个章节提供了技能和技能组总列表。技能以及专精的完整描述详见技能章节（P.128）。（译注：表略）<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">What The Numbers Mean<br>The first number in the skills column is the number of skill points a character has to spend on individual skills. These skill points are generally used to purchase Active skills, though they can be used for Knowledge and Language skills too (see below). If you don’t get exactly the skill ratings you want in this step, remember that skills may also be raised with Karma at the end of character creation. In this step, it only takes one skill priority point to either acquire a new skill or raise a skill rating by 1.<br>&nbsp; The number in the second column shows how many points characters can use on skill groups. Skill groups contain similar or complimentary skills that a player purchases as a bundle. When a skill group is purchased, the character is considered to have all the individual skills of the skill group at the rating of the group. the character wishes to break up the skill group during game play and raise only one of the skills, he is free to do so, but may not raise those skills as a skill group again until all skills possess the same rating. Skill group points may not be used to purchase individual skills and vice versa. In addition, skill groups cannot be broken up in this step, so individual skill points cannot raise the ratings of skills purchased as a group. (Note that skill groups can be broken up in Step Seven: Spend Your Left Over Karma (p. 98).<br>&nbsp; In character generation, the highest characters can raise a skill is 6 (7 if they purchase the Aptitude quality). After character generation, the highest rating a skill can hit is 12 (13 with the Aptitude quality).<br>&nbsp; All skill and skill group points must be spent at the time of character creation. These points cannot be saved or used after the game starts. The player should make sure any individual skills they want to purchase are not duplicated in any skill group they have taken. For example, a player may wish to purchase the Running skill, but if they have already purchased the Athletic skill group, the group includes running—they do not need to purchase the running skill a second time.<br>&nbsp; Along with skill ranks, players may also want to use their points to purchase specializations. Specializations are parts of a skill in which a character has invested extra time and effort, so they have become extra skilled. For example, if you have the Blades skill, you may specialize in an axe or survival knife. Having a specialization gives you a +2 dice pool bonus to skill tests involving the area of specialization.<br>&nbsp; At character creation, a specialization costs 1 skill point. No individual skill may have more than one specialization. As a character develops, though, they may gain other areas of expertise (for example, you may complement your axe knowledge with sword expertise) and so add more specializations to the same skills. Along with being purchased in this step, specializations may be purchased using Karma at the end of character creation (see Character Advancement, p. 103).<br>&nbsp; Specializations cannot be purchased for skill groups. Skill groups reflect a general understanding of similar skills rather than a particular expertise that a specialization denotes. Players may choose to buy a specialization for an individual skill within a skill group, but if they do so the skill group is broken from that point forward, meaning that all skills of the group must be raised separately. Additionally, once a specialization is taken for a skill in the skill group, it is impossible to reconstruct that skill group. This cannot happen in Step Five of character creation—you can only break up a skill group by buying a specialization for it in Step Seven (see p. 98 for details).<br>&nbsp; Survival on the streets depends on two things (at least): being really good at what you do, and having some backup skills for when things go to hell. If you’re going to be a shooter, stock up on the appropriate gun skills, but maybe add some Perception so you can see your targets coming, some Sneaking to keep them from seeing you, and some First Aid in case you wind up catching a bullet. If you’re a magician, you need plenty of Spellcasting, Counterspelling, and maybe Summoning, but Gymnastics might be a nice addition to help you avoid incoming attacks, and Palming may be useful for slipping a keycard from a guard while you’re invisible. And if you’re a face, you need plenty of social skills, but you’ll be asking for trouble if you don’t buy some combat skills to fall back on for those times when words fail you. Whatever your character concept, you should think of your character’s skills as a whole, building some excellent skills while also providing an overall balance to maximize your chances of success. You won’t have all your skills where you want them at first, but that’s why you play the game—as you finish missions and earn more Karma, you’ll have the chance to boost both your skills and your attributes.<br>&nbsp; For ease of reference, a master list of skill groups and skills are provided in this section. Full descriptions of skills and their specializations are found in the Skills chapter (p. 128).</div></div></div><br><strong>限制技能</strong><br>　　有些技能不是所有的人物都可以使用的。基于魔法或共鸣的技能就仅限于拥有魔法或共鸣属性的人物使用。如果没有适当的属性，人物不能学习或利用这些技能。这些限制技能罗列在P.151上技能列表中魔法和共鸣的栏目下。<br>　　此外，偏门魔法师只能使用一种类别的魔法技能（巫术、咒法或附魔），与此同时魔法师和神秘修士则可以使用全部这类技能。即使在矩阵中碟客的天赋与技术巫师如此相似，它们也还是不能使用基于共鸣的技能（编码、解码、注册）。技能限制以及人物是否能够学习某项技能的具体规则详见技能章节（P.128）。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Restricted Skills<br>There are some skills that cannot be used by all characters. Magic and Resonance-based skills are restricted to characters who have a Magic or Resonance attribute rating. Without the appropriate attribute, the character cannot learn or utilize these skills. These restricted skills are listed under the Magic and Resonance headings in the list of Individual Skills on p. 151.<br>&nbsp; Additionally, aspected magicians can use only one category of Magic skills (Sorcery, Conjuring, or Enchanting), while magicians and mystic adepts are able to use the whole range of skills. Deckers, even though many of their talents are similar to technomancers while in the Matrix, cannot use Resonance-based skills (namely Compiling, Decompiling, and Registering). For specifics on skill restrictions and whether a character can take a specific skill, refer to the Skills chapter (p. 128).</div></div></div><br><strong>知识和语言技能</strong><br>　　人物免费获得等于其（直觉等级＋逻辑等级）×2的知识和语言技能点数。这些点数的花费同其他技能点一样，也就是说1点换1级。<br>　　除了免费点数，你的人物还可以无需任何花费获得一门语言作为母语。在人物表中，这会在技能等级上标记一个“N”。如果你的人物选取了双母语特质，那你可以同样免费地选择第二门母语。<br>　　购买其他语言技能则会有数值等级。这个等级反映了人物对这门语言的理解和领悟有多深。只要人物至少有1级，人物就有可能用这门语言说、写，而且即便不能抓住细节也足够把握他所说、所写内容的要旨。更高的等级意味人物对这门语言掌握得更加熟练。在人物创建时，人物知识和语言技能的等级最高为6。语言技能使用直觉作为其关联属性。<br>　　知识技能有四种类别：学术、兴趣、专业和街头。根据类别，人物掷骰知识技能+直觉或知识技能+逻辑来通过检定。这些检定表明人物在一个具体问题上了解了什么信息，越多的净成功就表明人物在相关问题上越熟悉、了解得越多。学术知识是通过正规教育获得的信息，无论是学校、家教、大学或其他标准教育流程。兴趣包括爱好、经验和个别人物的个人兴趣。专业知识来自雇主或专业机构。街头知识包括了狂奔者在暗影中学到的所有东西，从毒品价格到帮派政治以及谁能为被盗物品给得最多（参见“知识类别范例表”（P.89）获得更多范例）。购买知识技能时，玩家应该注意他们为知识技能掷骰时，其技能类别关联哪个属性（直觉或逻辑）。有时，知识技能可以横跨多个类别。这种情况下，根据人物以及他们如何使用这些技能来选择知识技能的类别。例如，一个公司知识技能可以符合专业、学术或街头类别；拥有这个技能的新无政府主义者可能更关注公司活动如何影响街头生活，所以对这个人物来说，这个技能属于街头技能。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Knowledge and Language Skills<br>Characters receive free Knowledge and Language skills points equal to (Intuition rating + Logic rating) x 2. These points are spent in the same way as other skill points, meaning that spending 1 point gives 1 rank in a skill.<br>&nbsp; In addition to the free points, your character receives one language that he knows as a native language at no cost. On a character sheet, this is designated with an “N” as the skill rating. If your character has taken the Bilingual quality, you may have a second native language, which you also receive for free.<br>&nbsp; Additional Language skills are purchased and have numerical ratings. This rating represents how well the character understands and comprehends that language. As long as the character has at least a rating of 1, the character has a chance to be able to speak and/or write the language and to interpret the gist of what is said or written, even if they don’t catch every nuance. The higher the rating, the more fluent the character is in that language. At character creation, no character may possess a knowledge or a language skill higher than rating 6. Language skills use Intuition as their linked Attribute.<br>&nbsp; There are four types of Knowledge skills: Academic, Interests, Professional, and Street. Depending on the category, a character rolls either Knowledge skill + Intuition or Knowledge skill + Logic for the appropriate test. These tests indicate what information the character knows on a particular subject, with more net hits indicating that the character is more familiar with and has more knowledge of the subject in question. Academic knowledge is information gained through formal education, whether from a school, tutor, university, or other structured program. Interests include hobbies, experiences, and personal interests of the individual character. Professional knowledge comes from an employer or professional organization. Street knowledge includes everything a runner has picked up from life in the shadows, from drug prices to gang politics to who pays the most for stolen goods (see the Knowledge Category Examples table (p. 89) for more examples). When purchasing knowledge skills, a player should note which category the skill belongs to so they know which attribute (Intuition or Logic) they will need to roll on their Knowledge Tests. Sometimes, Knowledge skills may straddle multiple categories. In these cases, choose the most appropriate category for the knowledge skill based on the character and how they would use it. For example, a Corporations Knowledge skill could fit in Professional, Academic, or Street categories; a neo-anarchist with this skill would likely be focused on how corporate activities affect life on the street, so for this character it would be a Street skill.</div></div></div><br><strong>边栏——2075年常见知识技能</strong><br>黑市渠道、走私者、狂奔者藏身处、约翰逊先生、公司安保、掮客、机师、有组织犯罪、【城市】知识、街头帮派识别、公司政治、魔法理论、魔法威胁、化学、魔法组织、龙、神秘动物学、恶习、野外生存<br><br><strong>边栏——2075年常见语言</strong><br>赛普瑞希尔语（精灵语）、欧扎特语（兽人语）、英语、日语、普通话、俄语、法语、意大利语、德语、阿兹特兰西班牙语、西班牙语、拉科塔语、达科塔语、迪恩语（纳瓦乔语）<br><br><strong>知识类别范例</strong><br>类别　　关联属性　　范例<br>学术　　　逻辑　　　生物学、医学、魔法理论、政治、哲学、文学、历史、音乐、神秘植物学、神秘动物学<br>兴趣　　　直觉　　　时下储感电影、流行3D表演、20实际琐事、精灵果酒、都市格斗、战斗摩托、流行音乐<br>专业　　　逻辑　　　新闻业、商业、法律、军事服务<br>街头　　　直觉　　　帮派识别、犯罪组织、走私路线、销赃</div>
</div>
