<div class="post">
<div class="inner" id="msg_765298"><span style="font-size: 24pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>第六步</strong></span><br><span style="font-size: 18pt;" class="bbc_size"><strong>使用你的资源</strong></span><br>　　玩家应该只剩下一项优先级来分配给资源了。这个优先级决定了人物有多少钱能花在海扁别人或砸烂一个地方的装备上。可用装备见“街头装备”（P.421）。在这一步中，有将通过花钱提升你的人物；通过玩家业力的改进则在“第七步：使用你剩余的业力”中处理。<br>　　人物需要花掉他们绝大多数的新円；这一步结束时，他们可以选择保留至多5000新円，加在他们的起始新円上（P.95）。任何超过5000的部分将被弃除并且不能恢复。这一步中，新円不能被转换为业力，但玩家可以将一部分业力转换为新円，如果他们需要再多花一些的话。他们最多可以转换10业力，每点业力2000新円，也就说他们最多可以获得额外的20000新円。<br>　　<span style="color: blue;" class="bbc_color">如果玩家发现他剩下的新円超过了5000（没超过也一样），那这有几件创建一个暗影狂奔者要考虑的必备装备。你应该要一个通讯链（P.438）来保持联系，同时给你的装备在应对黑客时带来相对安全。一个假的SIN（P.442）以及相关的一些假证件，这有助于你应对执法或只是简单地买一张巴士车票或签下酒吧账单。更多内容见装备检查列表边栏。</span> <span style="color: red;" class="bbc_color">（勘误）</span>（该边栏略）<br>　　在购买装备时要记住三个限制。首先，购买如电子插件和生物插件这样的扩充物时，每个属性等级（精神和肉体）最多获得+4加值。如果提升的属性还没有达到天生最大限制，那么之后还能用业力对属性进行提升；但扩充物带来的加值不能超过+4。第二个限制，正常的人物创建中，人物受限于最大可用性等级12和设备等级6。在人物创建之后，人物可以通过装备获得更高的可用性（P.416）和更高的设备等级。最后，所有装备都必须得到游戏主持人的批准，即便这件装备在其他限制中都没有问题。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Step Six:<br>Spend Your Resources<br>Players should only have one Priority Level left to assign to Resources. This Priority Level determines the amount of money that characters will have to spend on the gear they’ll use to kick some ass, as well as a place to crash when the heat’s off. See Street Gear (p. 421) for available equipment. In this step, you’ll improve your character through spending money; any improvements made with the player’s Karma fund are handled in Step Seven: Spending Your Left Over Karma.<br>&nbsp; The character needs to spend the vast majority of nuyen they have; by the end of this step, they may choose to hold onto 5,000 nuyen or less and add it to their starting nuyen (p. 95). Any nuyen remaining over 5,000 is lost and cannot be recovered. While nuyen from this step cannot be converted to Karma, players can convert some of their Karma to nuyen if they need a little more to spend. They may convert up to 10 Karma at a rate of 2,000 nuyen per Karma point for gear, which means they can have up to 20,000 extra nuyen.<br>&nbsp; <del>When a character factors in racial modifiers for gear costs (trolls have a 50 percent gear and Lifestyle cost increase, dwarfs have a 10 percent increase in gear costs), the player may choose to increase the cost for each item picked up at that time to help them track how much they’ve spent and how much nuyen they have left. Alternately, they may choose to purchase all the gear at the base cost, arrive at a subtotal, and then add in the appropriate cost modifier (10 or 50 percent) to get the final total.</del><br>&nbsp; If the player finds that he or she has more than the 5,000 nuyen that can be saved (or even if he or she hasn’t), there are a few essential pieces of gear to consider when building a shadowrunner. You’ll want a commlink (p. 438) to stay in touch and to keep your gear relatively safe from hackers. A fake SIN (p. 442), along with some fake licenses, will help smooth dealing with law enforcement or even simple purchases like buying a bus ticket or covering a bar tab. For more ideas, see the Gear Checklist sidebar.<br>&nbsp; Keep in mind there are three restrictions when it comes to purchasing gear. First, when purchasing augmentations such as cyberware and bioware, each attribute rating (Mental and Physical) can only receive an augmentation bonus of up to +4. If the attribute being raised has not reached its natural maximum limit, the attribute can be raised naturally with Karma; but at no point can augmentations exceed the +4 bonus cap. The second restriction is that at normal character creation, characters are restricted to a maximum Availability rating of 12 and a device rating of 6. After character creation, characters may be able to acquire gear that has a higher Availability (p. 416) and a higher device rating. Finally, all gear is subject to gamemaster approval, even if the gear falls within these restrictions.</div></div></div><br><strong>电子插件和生物插件</strong><br>　　玩家用来增强他们人物属性的扩充物中，最常见是电子插件和生物插件（P.451）。电子插件是加强泛人类身体的技术，包括增强现有器官、肌肉和系统的性能或者用超越正常人类局限的人工制品完全替换掉泛人类身体的一部分。相反，生物插件是一种生长技术；细胞在实验室中成长并被设计为改善泛人类身体的天然状态，并加入一些天然不会存在的选项。电子插件通常比生物插件消耗更多人物的精华。生物插件的确定是更高昂的费用。<br>　　注意，如果人物选取了电子插件或生物插件，将会被移除一部分种族奖励。例如，如果玩家的精灵人物购买了电子眼，他们天生的低光视觉就会被移除，取而代之的是无论带有什么特性的电子眼。如果玩家依然想要低光视觉，她必须为电子眼选择低光视觉调整。同样，正色皮肤取代巨魔的天生皮肤，所以他不会从他天生的坚硬皮肤哪里获得额外的+1天生护甲。<br>　　电子插件和生物插件有四个等级可用：标准级、阿尔法级、贝塔级和德尔塔级（P.451）。人物创建时，只能选用标准级和阿尔法级。<br>　　电子插件和生物插件扩充物并不适合所有人。伴随增加的扩充物，魔法使用者和技术巫师在生理上会有损失精华的不良反应。在游戏中，这意味着任何精华的一部分损失都降低了魔法或共鸣属性1级。这意味着一个魔法5级的魔法师在购买并安装了电子眼（等级4），他们精华将从6减为5.5作为电子眼的精华花费，魔法师也将损失一整点的魔法，使他的魔法属性等级变为4。人物之后可以损失掉这一点精华中的另一半，降为5.0，同时不用承受魔法罚值，但一旦低于5.0，他的魔法等级就会再失去另一点。<br>　　这就是为什么很少有魔法使用者或技术巫师会安装电子插件或生物插件。那些这样做的人会发现他们的天赋被太多的扩充物燃烧殆尽，将他们的魔法或共鸣等级降为0。更多内容，见“魔法损失”（P.278）或“共鸣损失”（P.249）。<br>　　电子插件或生物插件提升的属性不会影响诸如知识技能点或人脉的结算。但是其他游戏中的机制，比如主动性和天生限制都将被扩充物调整，也就是说这些奖励要在“第八步：最终数字”（P.100）中考虑。当结算涉及精华的社交限制之前，将精华向上取整。<br>　　在人物表上需要记下扩充物。加上天生属性等级的合计应该用括号标注在天生属性旁以表示永久的增强等级。例如，天生力量等级4的人物拥有肌肉增强2级的生物插件应该这样记录他们的属性：力量4（6）。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Cyberware and Bioware<br>The most common augmentations players take to enhance their characters’ attributes are cyberware and bioware (p. 451). Cyberware is technology implanted into a metahuman body, either to enhance the performance of existing organs, muscles, and systems, or to replace a part of the metahuman body completely with an artificial form that exceeds normal human limitations. Bioware, by contrast, is living technology; cells grown in laboratories and designed to work within a metahuman’s body to improve on its natural design, and to add options nature never intended. Cyberware generally consumes more of a character’s Essence than bioware. The drawback for bioware is its greater expense.<br>&nbsp; Note that if a character takes cyberware or bioware, it may remove a particular racial bonus. For example, if a player who has an elf character buys cybereyes, their natural low-light vision is removed and replaced with the cybereyes and whatever attributes it possesses. If the player still wants low-light vision, she’ll have to select the low-light modification for the cybereyes. Similarly, orthoskin replaces the natural dermal deposits of a troll so he would no longer receive the +1 dermal armor from his natural skin hardness.<br>&nbsp; There are four grades of available cyberware and bioware: standard, alphaware, betaware, and deltaware (p. 451). Only standard gear and alphaware are available at character creation.<br>&nbsp; Cyberware and bioware augmentations are not for everyone. The physiologies for magic users and technomancers respond poorly to the loss of Essence that accompanies these augmentations. In game terms, this means that any fraction of Essence loss reduces a Magic or Resonance attribute rating by 1. This means that if a magician with Magic 5 decides to buy and install some cybereyes (Rating 4), their Essence will go from 6 to 5.5 due to the Essence cost of the cybereyes, and the magician will also lose a full point of Magic, leaving them with a Magic attribute rating of 4. The character can then lose another half a point of Essence, taking him down to 5.0, without a penalty to Magic, but if he drops below 5.0, his Magic rating is going to lose another point.<br>&nbsp; This is why so few magic users or technomancers make use of either cyberware or bioware. Those who do can find their talents burned out if too many augmentations reduce their Magic or Resonance rating to 0. For more information, see Magic Loss (p. 278) or Resonance Loss (p. 249).<br>&nbsp; Attributes boosted by cyberware or bioware do not affect the calculation for things such as points for Knowledge skills or Contacts. However, other in-game mechanics such as Initiative and Inherent Limits are modified by these augmentations, which means these bonuses need to be factored in during Step Eight: Final Numbers (p. 100). When calculating the Social limit using Essence, round your remaining Essence up to the nearest whole number before calculating the limit.<br>&nbsp; Augmentations need to be noted on the character sheet. The rating should be added to the natural attribute rating and the total written in parentheses next to the natural attribute rating to indicate the permanent augmented rating. For example, a character with a natural Strength rating of 4 and muscle augmentation 2 bioware should record their attribute as follows: Strength 4 (6).</div></div></div><br><strong>生活方式</strong><br>　　生活方式决定了人物生存下来需要的生活条件和每月费用。人物是否寄居在一栋废弃的建筑物里？他是否靠垃圾箱存货？人物是否住在破败的公寓里？人物是否找到了属于他自己的家？根据这些问题的答案，人物可以选择街头、寄居、低端、中端、高端或奢华的生活方式。详见P.373的生活方式。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Lifestyle<br>Lifestyle determines how the character lives and their monthly expenses so that they can survive. Is the character a squatter in an abandoned building? Does he survive by dumpster diving? Does the character live in a rundown apartment? Or has the character found a way to own her own home? Depending on the answers to these questions, the character may have a Street, Squatter, Low, Middle, High, or Luxury lifestyle. More information on lifestyles can be found on p. 373.</div></div></div><br><strong>起始新円</strong><br>　　在人物创建之后可以留下不超过5000新円来继续游戏。人物其余的起始新円取决于玩家为人物购买的生活方式，公式参见起始新円表。玩家根据指定骰数掷骰，然后适用人物生活方式提供的调整。结果加上购买装备后剩余的资金。<br><br><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px"><div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>剧透</b> - &nbsp;<i> </i>: <input type="button" value="顯示" style="width:60px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = ''; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;this.innerText = ''; this.value = '隐藏'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = '显示'; }"></div><div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;"><div style="display: none;">Starting Nuyen<br>No more than 5,000 nuyen (or less) of any unspent money from the funds available for character creation carries over to game play. The rest of the character’s starting nuyen is determined by the lifestyle the player has purchased for his character and the formula for that lifestyle specified by the Starting Nuyen Table. The player rolls the designated number of dice, then applies the modifier appropriate to their character’s Lifestyle. The result is added to any funds the player has left over after buying gear.</div></div></div><br><strong>生活方式花费表</strong><br>生活方式　　花费<br>街头　　　　免费　<br>寄居　　　　500<br>低端　　　　2000<br>中端　　　　5000<br>高端　　　　10000<br>奢华　　　　100000<br><br><strong>起始新円表</strong><br>生活方式　　起始新円<br>街头　　　　1D6×20<br>寄居　　　　2D6×40<br>低端　　　　3D6×60<br>中端　　　　4D6×100<br>高端　　　　5D6×500<br>奢华　　　　6D6×1000</div>
</div>
</div>
